# No Hard Wrapping

Do not hard-wrap prose at a fixed column width. Rely on the editor's soft wrapping instead. This applies to Markdown and other prose/text documents (`*.md`, `*.mdc`, `NOTICE`). `LICENSE` and verbatim third-party license text are exempt (keep legal text as-is). Source-code comments follow normal code style and are out of scope.

## Rules

- Write each paragraph as a **single physical line**. Do not insert newlines mid-sentence or mid-paragraph to fit ~80 columns.
- Keep one blank line between paragraphs.
- Each list item is its own line; do not wrap a single item across lines.
- Never reflow inside fenced code blocks, tables, or YAML frontmatter.

## Examples

❌ BAD — hard-wrapped paragraph:

```markdown
It integrates directly with the Resideo / Honeywell Home API and focuses
on doing one device type well: the water leak detector.
```

✅ GOOD — one line per paragraph (soft-wrapped by the editor):

```markdown
It integrates directly with the Resideo / Honeywell Home API and focuses on doing one device type well: the water leak detector.
```
